# Agent Harness Engineering — Deep Research Report

> Research compiled from: [AMP](https://ampcode.com/notes/how-to-build-an-agent), [LangChain](https://blog.langchain.com/improving-deep-agents-with-harness-engineering/), [OpenAI](https://openai.com/index/harness-engineering/), [Anthropic](https://www.anthropic.com/engineering/effective-harnesses-for-long-running-agents)

---

## What Is a "Harness"?

An agent harness is **the system that wraps around a language model** to turn it from a stateless text predictor into a reliable, tool-using agent. It's everything *except* the model weights: the loop, the tools, the middleware/hooks, the system prompt, the environment setup, and the persistence layer.

> **LangChain's definition:** *"The goal of a harness is to mold the inherently spiky intelligence of a model for tasks we care about."*

The harness is the engineering surface area that developers control. The model is a black box — the harness is how you shape its behavior, catch its failure modes, and make it reliable.

